cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as language modeling and next sentence prediction. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a multi-task learning approach to improve the performance of unsupervised pretraining models. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves training models to understand and generate natural language. It may also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses neural networks for pretraining and classification tasks. Finally, it could be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it involves training models to understand and classify visual and textual information.
